{
  "text": "Invariants (17) and (18) are the key invariants that relate the values of c(i) and y. Invariant [CITATION_1] implies that the network is synchronized. This is the main correctness property we are interested in. All the other invariants in Theorem 1 are auxiliary assertions, needed to make the invariant inductive.",
